Class DJIPhantomCamera

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.DJIObject
      • dji.sdk.api.Camera.DJICamera
        • dji.sdk.api.Camera.DJIPhantomCamera

  • public class DJIPhantomCamera
extends DJICamera

    Dji Phantom Camera Class

    Extending the DJICamera class, DJIPhantomCamera is specifically designed for Phantom.
    All the functions in DJIPhantomCamera is designed for getting & setting camera parameters, taking photos, recording videos, and receiving media data in SDcard.

    You could use this class to modify the parameter settings of photos and recordings so that they could satisfy your requirements. For example, if you want to adjust the size of photo you take, setCameraPhotoSize may help you to do that. With the help of the predefined enums, you could directly set up the parameters.
    Version:
    V2.4.0
    Author:
    DJI Software

      • startUpdateTimer

        public boolean startUpdateTimer(int interval)
        Start updating timer for receiving the instant information from the drone. This API will set up a timer for periodically invoking the DJIBatteryUpdateInfoCallBack, which could be set up by using setBatteryUpdateInfoCallBack.
        Please note that the interval could not be lower than 100ms.
        Overrides:
        startUpdateTimer in class DJICamera
        Parameters:
        interval - Timer run interval
        Returns:
        boolean true for successfully starting Update timer.
            false for informing failure.
        See Also:
